episodes.title: Episode #5.1
episodes.plot: Eight months after the last episode's events, a scandal breaks out when the story of Maloutru's death surfaces in the press.

episodes.title: Episode #5.2
episodes.plot: The Bureau is looking for César after he failed to catch a flight to Riga. Could he have been kidnapped? Meanwhile, Ellenstein is questioning JJA's power of judgment.

episodes.title: Episode #5.3
episodes.plot: Pavel Lebedev starts his job at the FSB. Bakatine, one of the Internal Security agents, is suspicious of him.

episodes.title: Episode #5.4
episodes.plot: Bakatine's ongoing investigation of Pavel Lebedev creates conflict with Karlov. JJA manages to track down the source of the article.

episodes.title: Episode #5.5
episodes.plot: Nadia and Pavel Lebedev spend some time together in Moscow, with Karlov's blessing. Marina comes to help Mille Sabord on the ground; he opens up to her again.

episodes.title: Episode #5.6
episodes.plot: Jonas goes to Cairo to strike a deal with the sheikh. Sisteron has to remain discreet as he goes about investigating JJA.

episodes.title: Episode #5.7
episodes.plot: Pavel Lebedev sees Nadia again. Mille Sabord is snooping around more than ever to find out about Malotru's past, making The Bureau very nervous.

episodes.title: Episode #5.8
episodes.plot: During a paper chase cleverly orchestrated by The Bureau and his friend Pavel Lebedev, Karlov slowly uncovers the vice that's tightening around him. Ready to recruit Karlov, Lebedev decides unilaterally to organize Nadia's extraction. This could sabotage the whole operation devised by JJA! The Bureau's director knows this is his last tour de force. Meanwhile, Bakatine is inches away from discovering the truth. It could all end in disaster.

episodes.title: Episode #5.9
episodes.plot: Having recently returned to France, Marie-Jeanne is put back in charge of The Bureau. Sisteron, meanwhile, is managing the office responsible for handling Intel from Karlov.

episodes.title: Episode #5.10
episodes.plot: A strange Uzbek tourist who has just settled in Paris finds a weapon left behind by Karlov.
